post0.title: Dog vision chatbot
post0.content: Overview . The goal of this project is to build a Telegram bot capable of telling a dog's breed from a photo of it. . To do this, I'll be using data from the Kaggle dog breed identification competition. It consists of a collection of 10,000+ labelled images of 120 different dog breeds. . For the model, I'm going to use a pretrained deep learning model from TensorFlow Hub (I'll be using TensorFlow to train a model leveraging Transfert Learning). . For the first part (getting data ready and training the model) I'm going to elaborate further (a lot) on a hands-on project from the zerotomastery Machine Learning Course. . For building the bot I'll follow this great post. . Data .
